// a key for an object must be regenerated if any of its collections keypair has changed or if a collection is removed from the object (verify all collections first)
// 

// a keypair for a collection must be regenerated if any of its groups keypair has changed or if a group is removed from the collection (verify all groups first)
// a collection can be verified if the sign(hash({publicKey, version, ...list of groups})) can be verified by a known admin group key (??? is storing needed or is implied verified groups enough ???)

// a keypair for a group must be regenerated if any of its users keypair has changed or if a user is removed from the group
// a group can be verified if the sign(hash({publicKey, version, ...list of users})) can be verified by a known admin key (stored on first group download)

// when a group is downloaded for the first time, the client stores the public sign keys of the group admins. 
// so that the server replaces the whole state after this moment, it would only be possible if the server has the group admin keypair

// when a group is created, the creating user signs the first log entry with their signature
// in the log entry is contained: a list of users
